@model AdMedWeb.Models.ContactForm

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About AdMed";
}

<div style="margin-left: 10%; margin-right: 10%;">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <br>
    <h3>Who are we? </h3>
    <p>
        AdMed is a non profit organisation, this foundation was built up by a group of young individuals who saw the need to implement this into our community and to strive to deliver excellence in the way in which we go about providing a service to the elderly.
        We have one aim within our company which is to provide a comfortable, hassle free, loving and caring environment for your loved ones.
        We promise to delivery quality service for your loved ones providing a group of widely ranged activities and socials to keep them entertained and mentally stimulated eliminating depression from the equation.
        AdMed has selected quality, friendly and caring staff members who are fully trained and ever ready to assist when needed.
        Trust us with your loved ones!
    </p>

    <br>
    <h3>Providing a central hub for information</h3>

    <p>
        Our website consists of a contact us page which gives you a clear indication of where we are. We have implemented a map view showing you the exact location as well as a satellite view for users to look for landmarks and to check out the area.
        Potential residents can show their interest by navigating to the Apply page and fill in their details. If you are or a loved one is interested in a warm and caring home, please do not hesitate to fill this application in, and a consultant will get back to you as soon as possible.
        We have also incorporated a contact form in which the user can drop us a message inquiring about any information that they are uncertain about, and we will have a consultant ready to provide any information that you need.
        Our website has many tabs that the user can look at, one that will catch the users eye will be the news tab which is our sites blog tab. Here you can see the activities that we offer for your loved ones as keeping them happy and fit both mentally and physically is high priority.
        Another Tab that provides a lot of resourceful information is the medication tab as this will be a concern of the user as your loved ones might require specific medication that has been assigned to them.
    </p>

    <br>
    <h3>Improving care for the aged</h3>

    <p>
        During the winter our staff provide your loved ones with thermals and warm bedding to suit their needs and keep them comfortable and warm.
        AdMed takes all of the users concerns into consideration and take positive action to implement them into our home. We want the users to feel safe in trusting us with your loved ones.
        We strive to bring excellence into our home. Everybody here is family and gets attended to in the highest possible manner.
        We value you!
    </p>
</div>